Owen_Busler:

you testing that? Displays true when reading the dio port and displaying it to the dashboard? If so can

Since the RIO has pullup resistors on all the DIO pins, it could be possible that the switch is connecting signal to 5v and therefore you will never see a change? Ideally you connect the signal to the NC and the ground to the common connection on the limit switch. Can we see a picture of that wiring?

Since the RIO has pullup resistors on all the DIO pins, it could be possible that the switch is connecting signal to 5v and therefore you will never see a change? Ideally you connect the signal to the NC and the ground to the common connection on the limit switch. Can we see a picture of that wiring?

Oh okay! When nothing is plugged into the DIO port, it will always read 5V.

You will need to put a connector like these at the end of your sensor wire: 36in PWM Cable - 4 Pack - REV Robotics

You will want to connect one end to Ground (black) and the other end to white (sense)

When the sensor detects the magnet, It will close the connection and then the d.get() will change value.
